The paper deals with computational geometry problems related to finding the minimal radius pair of congruent disks to cover a set of points in R^2. This falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also presents randomized algorithms and solutions for the (2,k)-center problem and the (p,k)-center problem, which involve optimization and algorithmic techniques, respectively. These topics are relevant to the sub-categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
